    <note>Zhou(1) Yi(2) [11559] See documentation for grandson, Mou [11561]. Hou [507] was the first Suichang Zhou jinshi in 1065, followed by Yi [476], jinshi in in 1070, and Shu [11564] (same generational name as Wan's [505] father Ti [11565]), jinshi in 1073). This seems hardly possible by coincidence and I am treating as two branches of the same root lineage. I done this by treating Yi(2) as chia=a and Congjian [11563] as his nephew and chia=b of zu 111. According to Yang(2) Shi's [2022] funerary inscription for Zhou(1) Wuzhong [7199] (q.v.), Zhou(1) H [16395], an unnamed ancestor of Wuzhong and descendant of Ren [16394] (the Han ancestor of the Runan Zhou), moved from Jingzhao to Chu, Suichang and I am assuming that Zhou H was also the ancestor of the other Suichang Zhou. I am making Wuzhong's lineage, which moved to Jianning at end of Tang, as chia 'c.'</note>
